{
  "phase": "question",
  "questions": [
    {
      "id": "q1",
      "question": "The existing test mocks `@/lib/api/client` but TradingPanel.test.tsx mocks `@/lib/query/hooks` instead. Since CreateMarketForm uses `useCreateMarket` from hooks (not the raw API client), should we mock `@/lib/query/hooks` (like TradingPanel) to control mutation state, or mock at the API layer?",
      "category": "design",
      "why_it_matters": "The TradingPanel pattern of mocking the hook gives direct control over isPending/isError/isSuccess states and the mutate function. The current test mocks @/lib/api/client which doesn't help test mutation state rendering. We need to decide the right mock layer."
    },
    {
      "id": "q2",
      "question": "CreateMarketForm calls `mutation.mutate(...)` with an `onSuccess` callback that navigates. TradingPanel tests don't test navigation. Should we mock `useNavigate` from react-router-dom, or rely on MemoryRouter's location tracking to verify post-creation navigation?",
      "category": "design",
      "why_it_matters": "Navigation testing requires either mocking useNavigate to assert it was called with `/markets/{id}`, or inspecting router state. The approach determines how we verify the success flow."
    },
    {
      "id": "q3",
      "question": "The `onSuccess` callback is passed inline to `mutation.mutate()` (line 54-58), not on the hook config. When we mock `useCreateMarket` to return a controlled mutate, should we capture and invoke the onSuccess callback manually to test navigation?",
      "category": "design",
      "why_it_matters": "Since onSuccess is passed to mutate() not to useMutation(), we need to capture it from mockMutate.mock.calls and manually invoke it with a fake response to trigger the navigate call. This is critical for testing the success flow."
    },
    {
      "id": "q4",
      "question": "The form has validation logic at line 62: `title.trim().length > 0 && expiresAt.length > 0 && outcomes.every(o => o.id && o.name)`. Should validation tests verify the submit button disabled state, or also test that form submission is prevented?",
      "category": "requirements",
      "why_it_matters": "The submit button is disabled when !isValid, so form submission is gated by button state. Testing just the disabled attribute may be sufficient, but we should confirm no other validation path exists."
    },
    {
      "id": "q5",
      "question": "The existing test already mocks `@/lib/api/client` at line 6. Should the new tests keep this mock and add `@/lib/query/hooks` mock, or replace the client mock entirely since we're mocking at the hook level?",
      "category": "codebase",
      "why_it_matters": "Having both mocks could cause confusion. Since we need to control mutation state (isPending, isError, etc.), the hook-level mock is necessary. The client mock may be redundant but removing it changes existing test behavior."
    },
    {
      "id": "q6",
      "question": "The `useSession` hook is used in CreateMarketForm (line 13) to get session.accountId for the mutate payload. Should we mock `useSession` like TradingPanel does, or does SessionProvider in renderWithProviders provide adequate defaults?",
      "category": "codebase",
      "why_it_matters": "If SessionProvider defaults to empty accountId/agentId, the component will pass `session: undefined` to mutate. We may need to mock useSession to test the session-passing logic in handleSubmit (line 52)."
    }
  ],
  "assumptions": [
    {
      "id": "a1",
      "assumption": "We should mock `@/lib/query/hooks` (useCreateMarket) at the hook level, following the TradingPanel pattern, rather than mocking the raw API client. This gives direct control over mutation state.",
      "confidence": 0.95,
      "if_wrong": "Would need to use a different approach like msw or a real QueryClient to test mutation lifecycle states."
    },
    {
      "id": "a2",
      "assumption": "We should mock `useNavigate` from react-router-dom to verify navigation after successful creation, and capture the onSuccess callback from mockMutate to invoke it manually with test data.",
      "confidence": 0.9,
      "if_wrong": "Would need to use MemoryRouter location state inspection or a different navigation testing approach."
    },
    {
      "id": "a3",
      "assumption": "The `useSession` hook needs to be mocked (like TradingPanel) to control accountId for testing the session-conditional logic on line 52.",
      "confidence": 0.85,
      "if_wrong": "SessionProvider default state might already provide testable values, making the mock unnecessary."
    },
    {
      "id": "a4",
      "assumption": "The existing 6 render tests should remain unchanged; new tests will be added alongside them in the same describe block.",
      "confidence": 0.95,
      "if_wrong": "Existing tests might need refactoring to work with the new mock setup (e.g., useCreateMarket mock needs a default return value)."
    },
    {
      "id": "a5",
      "assumption": "fireEvent is sufficient for testing form interactions (typing, clicking buttons). No need for userEvent library.",
      "confidence": 0.85,
      "if_wrong": "Some interactions like typing in inputs might need userEvent for more realistic simulation, especially if onChange handlers behave differently."
    },
    {
      "id": "a6",
      "assumption": "The remove outcome button (×) is disabled when outcomes.length <= 2, preventing removal below minimum. Tests should verify both the disabled state and the removal when 3+ outcomes exist.",
      "confidence": 0.95,
      "if_wrong": "Minor—would just adjust test expectations for the remove button behavior."
    },
    {
      "id": "a7",
      "assumption": "The outcome ID input sanitizes to lowercase alphanumeric + underscore (line 105). This validation happens in the onChange handler, not on submit, so tests should verify the sanitized value after input.",
      "confidence": 0.95,
      "if_wrong": "If sanitization is server-side or handled differently, test approach would need adjustment."
    }
  ],
  "spawn_children": false,
  "children": []
}

{
  "phase": "plan",
  "decisions": [
    {
      "id": "d1",
      "decision": "Mock @/lib/query/hooks (useCreateMarket) at the hook level instead of @/lib/api/client, following the TradingPanel pattern. Return a controlled mutation state object with isPending/isError/isSuccess/mutate.",
      "based_on": ["q1", "q5"],
      "alternatives_rejected": [
        "Keep existing @/lib/api/client mock — doesn't give control over mutation state rendering",
        "Use MSW to intercept HTTP requests — too heavy for unit tests and harder to control state transitions"
      ],
      "reversibility": "easy"
    },
    {
      "id": "d2",
      "decision": "Mock useNavigate from react-router-dom using vi.importActual pattern. Capture the onSuccess callback from mockMutate.mock.calls and invoke it manually with fake response data to test navigation.",
      "based_on": ["q2", "q3"],
      "alternatives_rejected": [
        "MemoryRouter location tracking — more complex and less direct than asserting on mock",
        "Skip navigation testing — leaves a critical user flow untested"
      ],
      "reversibility": "easy"
    },
    {
      "id": "d3",
      "decision": "Mock useSession from @/features/session/context using vi.importActual pattern, returning controlled session with accountId for mutation payload tests.",
      "based_on": ["q6"],
      "alternatives_rejected": [
        "Rely on SessionProvider defaults — empty accountId means session is always undefined in mutate payload, can't test the truthy path"
      ],
      "reversibility": "easy"
    },
    {
      "id": "d4",
      "decision": "Test validation via submit button disabled state only. No need to test form submission prevention separately since the disabled button blocks clicks.",
      "based_on": ["q4"],
      "alternatives_rejected": [
        "Test both button state and submission prevention — redundant since disabled button already blocks clicks"
      ],
      "reversibility": "easy"
    },
    {
      "id": "d5",
      "decision": "Replace existing @/lib/api/client mock with @/lib/query/hooks mock. Add a beforeEach that sets up defaultMutationState() so existing 6 render tests continue to work.",
      "based_on": ["q5"],
      "alternatives_rejected": [
        "Keep both mocks — confusing and the client mock is redundant when hook is mocked"
      ],
      "reversibility": "easy"
    },
    {
      "id": "d6",
      "decision": "Use fireEvent (not userEvent) for all interactions, consistent with TradingPanel test pattern.",
      "based_on": ["q1"],
      "alternatives_rejected": [
        "userEvent — not used in the project, would add a new dependency pattern"
      ],
      "reversibility": "easy"
    }
  ],
  "steps": [
    {
      "step": 1,
      "task": "Refactor mock setup: Replace vi.mock('@/lib/api/client') with vi.mock('@/lib/query/hooks') returning { useCreateMarket: vi.fn() }. Add vi.mock('react-router-dom') with vi.importActual preserving all exports but mocking useNavigate. Add vi.mock('@/features/session/context') with vi.importActual preserving all exports but mocking useSession. Create defaultMutationState() helper returning { mutate: vi.fn(), isPending: false, isError: false, isSuccess: false, error: null, data: undefined, reset: vi.fn() }. Add beforeEach that sets default return values for all three mocks.",
      "depends_on": []
    },
    {
      "step": 2,
      "task": "Verify existing 6 render tests still pass with the new mock setup. Run vitest on CreateMarketForm.test.tsx and fix any breakage.",
      "depends_on": [1]
    },
    {
      "step": 3,
      "task": "Add validation tests: (a) submit button disabled when title is empty, (b) submit button disabled when expiresAt is empty, (c) submit button disabled when an outcome has empty id, (d) submit button disabled when an outcome has empty name, (e) submit button enabled when all fields are valid (title, expiresAt, and outcomes all populated).",
      "depends_on": [2]
    },
    {
      "step": 4,
      "task": "Add form interaction tests: (a) typing in title updates preview text from 'Untitled market' to the typed value, (b) clicking '+ Add outcome' adds a third outcome row, (c) remove outcome button (×) is disabled when exactly 2 outcomes, (d) remove outcome button removes an outcome when 3+ outcomes exist, (e) outcome ID input sanitizes to lowercase alphanumeric + underscore (typing 'Hello World!' results in 'helloworld').",
      "depends_on": [2]
    },
    {
      "step": 5,
      "task": "Add mutation state rendering tests: (a) submit button shows 'Creating…' and is disabled when mutation.isPending is true, (b) error message div appears with mutation.error.message when mutation.isError is true, (c) error message shows 'Failed to create market' when error is not an Error instance.",
      "depends_on": [2]
    },
    {
      "step": 6,
      "task": "Add submission and navigation tests: (a) clicking submit calls mockMutate with correct payload structure { payload: { title, description, outcomes, expires_at, liquidity }, session }, (b) when onSuccess callback is invoked with { market: { id: 'test-123' } }, navigate is called with '/markets/test-123', (c) when session.accountId is empty, session is passed as undefined in the mutate payload.",
      "depends_on": [2]
    },
    {
      "step": 7,
      "task": "Run full test suite (vitest run) to ensure no regressions. Fix any failures.",
      "depends_on": [3, 4, 5, 6]
    }
  ],
  "spawn_children": false,
  "children": []
}

